SUMMARY:Young People's Chamber Orchestra
DESCRIPTION:The Young People’s Chamber Orchestra is a youth string orchestra working without a conductor. It is modeled after the Bay Area’s renowned New Century Chamber Orchestra and is the first youth ensemble of its kind in northern California. Currently under the direction of Aaron Westman\, the orchestra has been featured as a guest on a New Century Chamber Orchestra performance and has been a winner of the Berkeley Junior Bach Festival.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/young-peoples-chamber-orchestra/
LOCATION:Cloverdale Performing Arts Center\, 209 N. Cloverdale Blvd.\, Cloverdale\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
