SUMMARY:Public Star Party
DESCRIPTION:Public Star Parties are the heart of the Robert Ferguson Observatory—your monthly invitation to experience the wonder of the night sky like never before. Whether you’re a lifelong astronomy enthusiast or simply curious about what lies beyond our planet\, these gatherings offer something magical for everyone. \nEach month includes a variety of engaging astronomy presentations led by our expert docents. You’ll hear fascinating stories about the cosmos and the science behind some of the objects you’ll soon be observing. These talks set the stage for an unforgettable night under the stars. \nStep outside into the darkness of Sugarloaf Ridge State Park\, where the skies open up in breathtaking clarity. You’ll have the chance to explore the universe through three of RFO’s massive telescopes\, each powerful enough to reveal extraordinary detail: lunar craters\, planets\, star clusters\, glowing nebulae\, distant galaxies\, and more. In addition\, a field of smaller telescopes brought and operated by dedicated volunteers\, creates a dynamic\, community-powered observing experience. \nEvery month offers a new selection of celestial treasures\, and our friendly\, knowledgeable docents are excited to guide you. They’ll help you navigate the night sky\, answer questions\, and point out objects that many people never get the chance to see. \nCome experience the excitement\, curiosity\, and shared sense of discovery that make Public Star Parties such a cherished RFO tradition. Free for members—and unforgettable for everyone!
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/public-star-party-3/
LOCATION:Robert Ferguson Observatory\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Road\, Kenwood\, CA
CATEGORIES:Kids and Family,Other,Recreation
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Star-party-robert-ferguson-observatory-1s.jpg
GEO:38.4427;-122.533
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Robert Ferguson Observatory 2605 Adobe Canyon Road Kenwood CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=2605 Adobe Canyon Road:geo:-122.533,38.4427
END:VEVENT
